@idiotperson I personally think that through their perception their world looks like how we perceive their world. I assume that whoever imagines this helps creates it, and it would be created through their lens. That would answer the question of how their world look; it would look like however we imagine it. This would mean that, for them, their world would look exactly like how we see it. Now to the case of how anime and live action would look. Like I said earlier whenever we see a anime/manga character watching or reading anime/manga the anime/manga is usually in the same art style as the original medium. I would assume that anime and manga would look completely the same as their world would due to us seeing it as the same however, they would see a difference as it would not look completely real. Since we live on a different plane of existince we cannot see the difference but they, would see the difference as they exist in that world. All of this is under the assumption they exist.

This was pretty dang good! I looked at some of the artist's other stuff and they seem promising.  But reading this reminded me of something.  When we see her drawings, we see them as being in the anime style, which makes sense. However, in the world the characters experience, would it appear to be realistic to them or would it appear as also being in a cartoon-like style as it is for us.  In certain shows, characters will explicitly say that they are watching anime, and, to us at least, it looks indistinguishable from any supposed "live action" shows (as in, shows in the universe of a given show).  So do if anime is the same thing as live action for them, do they see the world as entirely anime or do they see the world how we see our world? And perhaps, in their world, their are differences between "live action" and anime, but they are imperceptible to our human eye.  Much to consider
